text: Middlesex County, New Jersey is a borough of Middlesex County, New Jersey, United States. As of the 2020 United States Census, the borough's population was 14,636. Middlesex was incorporated as a borough on April 9, 1913.Snyder, John P. The Story of New Jersey's Civil Boundaries: 1606-1968, Bureau of Geology and Topography; Trenton, New Jersey; 1969. p. 170. Accessed September 4, 2012. In 1905, the Lincoln section of Middlesex organized a volunteer fire company. == References == Category:Boroughs in New Jersey Category:Middlesex County, New Jersey Category:1913 establishments in the United States Category:20th-century establishments in New Jersey
